Threshold Evaluation helps you optimize the threshold value for a model. The threshold value tells your model how to classify a binary outcome.

Navigate to Threshold Evaluation in Performance, click on it.

Metrics on the Threshold Evaluation Tab:
Controls: Set an optimal threshold by dragging a slider or selecting a metric.
Cost Ratio: Specify a cost ratio (false positives and false negatives) to optimize the threshold.

ROC Curve: Displays performance measurements at various threshold settings. The blue dot moves along the Actual Model line, representing the threshold value on the ROC curve.

Y-axis: True Positive Rate
X-axis: False Positive Rate
Model (blue line)
No Model (gray line)

Number of Rows
AUC (Area Under the Curve): Represents the rate of correct classification by a logistic model. An AUC of 0.5 means random guessing, an AUC of 1.0 means perfect classification.

Metrics for Binary Classification Use Cases
